President Obama has nominated Vernon S. Broderick to serve on the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York. Broderick is currently a partner at the law firm Weil, Gotshal & Manges LLP and specializes in white collar criminal cases, regulatory investigations, and business litigation. He has also served as an Assistant United States Attorney and has been appointed to various commissions by Governor Andrew Cuomo and Mayor Michael Bloomberg. Broderick holds a J.D. from Harvard Law School and a B.A. from Yale University.